XGB (eXtreme Gradient Boosting) is an optimized ensemble algorithm based on the gradient boosting decision tree, which can build CARTs (Classification and Regression Trees) efficiently and operate in parallel. Assume that a dataset with n states’ data in the US is Dn ×  m = {(xi, yi),  xi ∈  Rm,  yi ∈ R,  i =  1,  2,  …,  n} in which xi is i-th state of m dimension vector, in which m represents the number of static attributes. In this study, yi is the true value of the infection rate, i.e. the total number of the confirmed cases per 1000 people, of i-th state. The estimation of infection rate in the light of XGB was obtained by summarizing K additive CARTs as Eq. (2).
